<chapter xml:id="ch_circ-res" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Circuits: Resistors</title>
	<introduction>
    <p> In this chapter you will learn about resistors in circuits.</p>
	
	</introduction>
		
    <objectives>
      
      <introduction><p>After successful completion of this chapter, you will be able to:</p></introduction>
		<ol>
			<li><p>Determine the amount of current flowing through a circuit with one or more resistors and a single battery, both quantitatively and qualitatively.</p></li>
			<li><p>Determine the amount of current flowing through a circuit with one or more resistors and more than one battery, both quantitatively and qualitatively.</p></li>
			<li><p>Determine the equivalent resistance of a circuit.</p></li>
			<li><p>Determine the power and/or energy used by a resistor.</p></li>
		</ol>
	</objectives>

